.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Thread \- NIP\-10 text note threading
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Thread;
\&
\&    # Create a direct reply to a root post
\&    my $reply = Net::Nostr::Thread\->reply(
\&        to      => $root_event,
\&        pubkey  => $my_pubkey,
\&        content => \*(AqGreat post!\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Create a reply to a reply
\&    my $deep_reply = Net::Nostr::Thread\->reply(
\&        to        => $reply_event,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        content   => \*(AqI agree\*(Aq,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com/\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Quote an event
\&    my $quote = Net::Nostr::Thread\->quote(
\&        event   => $original,
\&        pubkey  => $my_pubkey,
\&        content => \*(AqLook at this nostr:nevent1...\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse thread info from an event
\&    my $thread = Net::Nostr::Thread\->from_event($event);
\&    if ($thread) {
\&        say "Root: " . $thread\->root_id;
\&        say "Reply to: " . $thread\->reply_id if $thread\->reply_id;
\&    }
\&
\&    # Check if an event is a reply
\&    say "is reply" if Net::Nostr::Thread\->is_reply($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-10 text note threading for kind 1 events. Provides methods
to create properly tagged reply and quote events, and to parse thread
structure from existing events.
.PP
Uses marked \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags (preferred) with \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`reply\*(C'\fR markers.
Also parses deprecated positional \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags for backward compatibility.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $thread = Net::Nostr::Thread\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Thread\*(C'\fR object.  Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $thread = Net::Nostr::Thread\->new(
\&        root_id    => \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32,
\&        root_relay => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`root_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`root_relay\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`root_pubkey\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`reply_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`reply_relay\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`reply_pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`mentions\*(C'\fR (defaults
to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`root_id\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`reply_id\*(C'\fR are validated as 64\-character lowercase hex
strings. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS reply
.IX Subsection "reply"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Thread\->reply(
\&        to         => $parent_event,
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content    => \*(Aqreply text\*(Aq,
\&        relay_url  => \*(Aqwss://relay.com/\*(Aq,   # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&        created_at => time(),               # optional, passed to Event
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1 reply event with proper marked \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags and \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags.
A direct reply to a root post gets a single \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag with marker \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR.
A reply to a reply gets two \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags: \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`reply\*(C'\fR, sorted by
reply stack (root first).
.PP
The reply\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags include the parent author and all of the parent\*(Aqs
\&\f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags, deduplicated, excluding the replier\*(Aqs own pubkey.
.PP
Croaks if the parent event is not kind 1 (use NIP\-22 for other kinds).
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    # Direct reply to root
\&    my $reply = Net::Nostr::Thread\->reply(
\&        to => $root, pubkey => $pk, content => \*(Aqhello\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # tags: [[\*(Aqe\*(Aq, $root_id, \*(Aq\*(Aq, \*(Aqroot\*(Aq, $root_pubkey], [\*(Aqp\*(Aq, $root_pubkey]]
\&
\&    # Reply to a reply
\&    my $deep = Net::Nostr::Thread\->reply(
\&        to => $mid_reply, pubkey => $pk, content => \*(Aqhi\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # tags: [[\*(Aqe\*(Aq, $root_id, \*(Aq\*(Aq, \*(Aqroot\*(Aq, ...], [\*(Aqe\*(Aq, $mid_id, \*(Aq\*(Aq, \*(Aqreply\*(Aq, ...], ...]
.Ve
.SS quote
.IX Subsection "quote"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Thread\->quote(
\&        event     => $quoted_event,
\&        pubkey    => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content   => \*(Aqlook at this nostr:nevent1...\*(Aq,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.com/\*(Aq,   # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1 event with a \f(CW\*(C`q\*(C'\fR tag referencing the quoted event.
The quoted event\*(Aqs author is added as a \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag unless the quoter
is the same pubkey (no self\-reference).
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $qt = Net::Nostr::Thread\->quote(
\&        event => $original, pubkey => $pk, content => \*(Aqwow\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # tags: [[\*(Aqq\*(Aq, $original_id, \*(Aq\*(Aq, $original_pubkey], [\*(Aqp\*(Aq, $original_pubkey]]
.Ve
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $thread = Net::Nostr::Thread\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses thread structure from an event\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags. Returns a
\&\f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Thread\*(C'\fR object, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the event has no \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags.
.PP
Prefers marked \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags (with \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`reply\*(C'\fR markers). Falls back to
deprecated positional parsing for unmarked tags.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $thread = Net::Nostr::Thread\->from_event($event);
\&    say $thread\->root_id;
\&    say $thread\->reply_id if $thread\->reply_id;
.Ve
.SS is_reply
.IX Subsection "is_reply"
.Vb 1
\&    my $bool = Net::Nostr::Thread\->is_reply($event);
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the event has any \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags indicating it is a thread reply.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    if (Net::Nostr::Thread\->is_reply($event)) {
\&        my $thread = Net::Nostr::Thread\->from_event($event);
\&        ...
\&    }
.Ve
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS root_id
.IX Subsection "root_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $thread\->root_id;
.Ve
.PP
The event ID of the thread root.
.SS root_relay
.IX Subsection "root_relay"
.Vb 1
\&    my $relay = $thread\->root_relay;
.Ve
.PP
Relay URL hint for the root event, or empty string.
.SS root_pubkey
.IX Subsection "root_pubkey"
.Vb 1
\&    my $pk = $thread\->root_pubkey;
.Ve
.PP
Public key of the root event author, if available.
.SS reply_id
.IX Subsection "reply_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $thread\->reply_id;
.Ve
.PP
The event ID of the direct parent, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for direct replies to root.
.SS reply_relay
.IX Subsection "reply_relay"
.Vb 1
\&    my $relay = $thread\->reply_relay;
.Ve
.PP
Relay URL hint for the parent event, or empty string.
.SS reply_pubkey
.IX Subsection "reply_pubkey"
.Vb 1
\&    my $pk = $thread\->reply_pubkey;
.Ve
.PP
Public key of the parent event author, if available.
.SS mentions
.IX Subsection "mentions"
.Vb 1
\&    my $ids = $thread\->mentions;  # arrayref
.Ve
.PP
Event IDs from deprecated positional \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags that are neither root nor
reply (the "middle" tags). Empty arrayref for marked tags.
